      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you are moving to an API-driven, stateless model, the most critical element you are losing is the internal state management provided by `StateManager` within `AgenticRuntime`. Dropping it means any function that relied on the runtime maintaining context across multiple calls will immediately fail, as that context is now externalized to the database. You must ensure that the new `StatelessExecutor` is correctly receiving and utilizing the necessary session or task context from the API payload to prevent immediate operational failure.",
      "source": "target",
